<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 4:08PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER SUNDAY...
West-northwest winds 10 to 20 mph, with gusts to 25 mph will occur
Sunday especially from noon to 6pm. Humidity levels will fall to
15 to 25 percent in the afternoon. This will result in increased
fire danger.
Residents are urged to exercise caution handling any potential
ignition source...including machinery... cigarettes...and matches.
Be sure to properly discard all smoking materials. Any dry
grasses and tree litter that ignite will have the potential to
spread quickly.</description>
